{"questionId":"14472498","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form at least one equation, using either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mrow></msub></math>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>13</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve simultaneous linear equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> by substituting or eliminating one of the variables.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: If candidate does not explicitly state their values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>, but gives <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></math>, award final two marks as <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form at least one equation, using either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>26</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><strong>and</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve simultaneous linear equations in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> by substituting or eliminating one of the variables.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>If candidate does not explicitly state their values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>, do not award the final mark.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14472498","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ2.4a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of p and the value of q.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}